# Spacewalk Server Installation

Build notes for standing up an Oracle Spacewalk (Oracle Linux Manager) server on Oracle Linux 6, backed by an **external Oracle database**. Covers the Instant Client setup, repo configuration, a dependency workaround, and the `spacewalk-setup` walkthrough.

> All hostnames, IP addresses, accounts, and email addresses below are generic placeholders.

## 1. Update the base system

The package source must be the Oracle public yum repo.

```bash
yum update
```

## 2. Install the Oracle Instant Client

```bash
rpm -ivh oracle-instantclient11.2-basic-11.2.0.4.0-1.x86_64.rpm \
         oracle-instantclient11.2-sqlplus-11.2.0.4.0-1.x86_64.rpm
```

Add the client library path to `ldconfig`:

```bash
echo /usr/lib/oracle/11.2/client64/lib > /etc/ld.so.conf.d/oracle-instantclient11.2.conf
ldconfig
```

## 3. Exclude the jta package

The Spacewalk server fails to start if the `jta` package is installed. Confirm it is not present:

```bash
yum list installed | grep jta
```

Prevent future installation by adding an exclusion to `/etc/yum.conf`:

```ini
# Prevent jta package installation — Spacewalk server start-up fails if jta is installed.
exclude=jta*
```

## 4. Configure the Spacewalk repositories

Create `/etc/yum.repos.d/spacewalk26.repo`:

```ini
[ol6_spacewalk26_server]
name=Spacewalk Server 2.6 for Oracle Linux 6 ($basearch)
baseurl=http://yum.oracle.com/repo/OracleLinux/OL6/spacewalk26/server/$basearch/
gpgkey=file:///etc/pki/rpm-gpg/RPM-GPG-KEY-oracle
gpgcheck=1
enabled=1

[ol6_spacewalk26_client]
name=Spacewalk Client 2.6 for Oracle Linux 6 ($basearch)
baseurl=http://yum.oracle.com/repo/OracleLinux/OL6/spacewalk26/client/$basearch/
gpgkey=file:///etc/pki/rpm-gpg/RPM-GPG-KEY-oracle
gpgcheck=1
enabled=1
```

## 5. Install the Spacewalk server packages

```bash
yum install spacewalk-oracle spacewalk-utils spacecmd
```

### Dependency error and resolution

The install may fail with:

```text
/usr/bin/rebuild-jar-repository: error: JAVAVER_LIBDIR /usr/share/java-1.7.0 does not exist or is not a directory
```

Resolution:

```bash
cd /etc/yum.repos.d/
cp -p public-yum-ol6.repo.rpmsave public-yum-ol6.repo

yum remove groovy15-1.5.6-2.jpp5.noarch
mkdir /usr/lib/java-1.7.0
mkdir /usr/share/java-1.7.0
yum install groovy15-1.5.6-2.jpp5.noarch

yum install spacewalk-oracle spacewalk-utils spacecmd
rm -f public-yum-ol6.repo
```

Afterwards, disable the repos in `/etc/yum.repos.d/spacewalk26.repo`.

## 6. Add host entries

Add the relevant hosts to `/etc/hosts`:

```text
10.0.0.11    spacewalk01.example.net    spacewalk01
10.0.0.12    oradb01.example.net        oradb01
10.0.0.25    mail01.example.net         mail01
```

Test connectivity to the database listener:

```bash
curl -v telnet://10.0.0.12:1521
```

